title: For Sale:  Savage 10ML II Smokeless Muzzleloader
postcontent: Savage 10ML II Smokeless Muzzleloader. .50 cal. These are not made anymore, and are hard to come by. Factory plastic stock has been replaced by a wood Savage factory short action stock and has had the action pillar bedded and glassed, including the popular 3rd pillar conversion. This conversion is desired by many who seriously shoot a Savage Smokeless Muzzleloader because it allows removal of the breech plug without losing zero. The wooden stock was not modified to have the ramrod held in it, preferring to keep the forend stiffer, and carry the ramrod separately like many of the long-range shooters of smokeless muzzleloaders. The breech plug removal tools are included, and I will also provide the original factory plastic stock and the ramrod thimble in the event you want to return it to the factory setup. The wooden stock is in really good condition, with only a few minor dings. The metal is in terrific condition with little to no wear on the bluing. To increase accuracy, the original QLA (quick-load assist) was removed from the end of the barrel, and the barrel re-crowned. Two index marks were also added on the crown so that the sabots could be indexed to the rifling. The muzzleloader consistently shot 1" groups, at 2250 fps, with a Hornady 250SST, using a Savage recommended load. I am also including a ramrod carrying pouch. If you want to learn more about the Savage Smokeless Muzzleloader, look up "Doug's Message Boards" and find the Savage/Smokeless Muzzleloading section. Will ship. Will consider trades, especially for S&W 629 44 mag with 4" bbl.
